A farmer in his late 70s and his employee were attacked at his farm in Umlaas Road, in Camperdown, yesterday afternoon. According to Shaheen Sulieman of Magma Security, the farmer and the employee were tied up by two men who attacked them. “They beat them up and took electronics, jewellery and money from the house. The employer managed to escape and called the control room for assistance,” said Sulieman. ALSO READ | Another brutal farm attack in KZN He added the two men were later arrested by Magma security and the things they had taken from the house were recovered. Sulieman said the farmer is recovering at the hospital. Police had not responded to The Witness’ media query at the time of publication.